    {
        "content": "<p>the main issue here is that addition is defined to recurse on the right, so you have a much easier time proving this by either swapping <code>m + n</code> to <code>n + m</code> in the resulting vector size, or by recursing on the right argument in vec_append (somehow)</p>",
        "id": 492748373,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1736436154
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>because lean has no issue seeing <code>n + 0 = n</code> or <code>n + (m + 1) = (n + m) + 1</code>, since these precisely the cases in the definition of addition on naturals</p>",
        "id": 492748687,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1736436237
